data.name: infoBox.Text
data.value:
Pi is a mathematical constant that is very closely related to circles. Pi is the english spelling of the greek letter π, which is also used to represent the same number.
But to understand Pi, we first have to look at the different parts of a circle.

data.name: infobox2infobox2.Text
data.value: The Circumference is the distance around the circle. The Diameter is the distance across the circle, going through the centre. The Radius is the distance from the centre to the edge, equal to half the diameter.

data.name: Label1.Text
data.value: If we take a circle of diameter 1 and roll it accross a number line, after one full rotation the circle would have travelled Pi units. This is because Pi is the ratio of the Circumference to the Diameter. Pi is an infinitely long decimal number, so for simplicity we will use 3 because it is the closest integer.
